- The integer array parameter `weights` must not be null.
- The integer array parameter `weights` must have a length greater than or equal to 1 and less than or equal to 50000.
- All values in the integer array parameter `weights` must be greater than or equal to 1 and less than or equal to 500.
- The integer parameter `days` must be greater than or equal to 1 and less than or equal to the length of the integer array parameter `weights`.
- The integer result is the least weight capacity of the ship that will result in all the packages on the conveyor belt being shipped within `days` days.